	   <tr><td colspan=2>This week I am moving home so I am updating early this week.<br><br>This week’s rant proposes what would be in a license agreement if a Verant conduct clause existed. This can but substituted with any online company but I am using Verant as an example.<br><br>Conduct Clause.<br>By using this product, you have given Sony Online Entertainment Inc. and Verant Interactive inc. the express right to treat you like garbage, act like kings, nerf characters without warning, not fix bugs and lie to you about the previous actions. By agreeing to this license you hereby agree to throw your money at said corporations without guarantee of fun and enjoyment.   We also reserve the right to prevent you from playing Everquest for any reason and can take down the servers without reason or warning. You have also given us the right to force you to wait days for spawns, take 12 hours to gain one bubble of experience and work with jerks. You have also absolved Everquest Customer service of any responsibilities pertaining to customer service. We will, at anytime ignore any and all petitions pertaining to real issues including, bugs, camp issues and missing inventory. If you at any time make us look to be wrong in any situation, you will be banned and all blame will be thrown upon you.<br>Enjoy!!!<br><br>My technical writing is not that great, but the general idea is there.<br>Roshi out.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>current Doac Player;<br>Former eq player.</td></tr>
