<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100811145285776></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100811145285776><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100811145285776>RE: conduct clause</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100811145285776#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Sage>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>93 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 11th 5:57 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.06]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><b>Conduct Clause. </b><br><i>By using this product, you have given Sony Online Entertainment Inc. and Verant Interactive inc. the express right to treat you like garbage, act like kings, nerf characters without warning, not fix bugs and lie to you about the previous actions.</i><br>Actually, you agree to this all the time.  If you buy any online game, the provider is entitled to make whatever changes they wish.  SOE maybe do this a little more freely than anyone else, but the fact is, they are currently the king of the heap in MMORPG's.<br><br><i>By agreeing to this license you hereby agree to throw your money at said corporations without guarantee of fun and enjoyment.</i><br>In the UK, Trading standards laws state that, 'a product must be fit for the purpose it is purported to serve.'  This doesn't actually mean you have to like it.  It just has to do what it says it does.  Have you ever bought a book that comes with a money back guarantee, if you find it boring???<br><br><i>We also reserve the right to prevent you from playing Everquest for any reason and can take down the servers without reason or warning.</i><br>There's always a warning for the normal monthly patches.  (It always catches me offguard, but that's 'cos I don't check when it is.)  At the moment there is mass patching, which is a pain in the ass.  But, surely you can't claim it's without reason?  (It's a sign of poor testing, but that's a different issue.  Maybe on you should apply a rant to, huh?)<br><br><i>You have also given us the right to force you to wait days for spawns, take 12 hours to gain one bubble of experience and work with jerks.</i><br>You know, I camped the AC in OoT a coupla weeks ago.  Almost twenty hours I spent on it and no AC spawn.  *Sigh*  Still, I don't remember being forced into doing it.  <br>If it takes you twelve hours to gain a bubble of experience, you're either at a far higher level than me, or you suck!  *Grin*<br>Now, I <b>have</b> been forced to wor with jerks.  But that's at university and it's a part of my course.  No-one ever forced me to work with jerks in EQ.  Sure, there are plenty around, but there're a fair few of 'em in RL.  You don't even have to hear them!  That's what /ignore is for!<br>No-one is forced into anything.  You don't even have to play, if you don't wanna, let alone play in a specific way.<br><br><i>You have also absolved Everquest Customer service of any responsibilities pertaining to customer service. We will, at anytime ignore any and all petitions pertaining to real issues including, bugs, camp issues and missing inventory.</i><br>Lotsa companies do this.  It's a nice cosy part of being in a field on your own.  (Don't tell me DAoC is competition.  It's not really in any significant way.)<br><br><i>If you at any time make us look to be wrong in any situation, you will be banned and all blame will be thrown upon you.</i><br>Now here we're getting into the attitude of governments.  If you give someone power over you, this is what happens.  (Have you ever heard the phrase, &quot;Don't steal: The government doesn't like competition!&quot;<br><br><i>Enjoy!!! </i><br>Well, this bit is nice, no?<br><br>Anyway, good luck with moving.<br><br>When you get back, give serious thought to writing about the whole SoL farce.  I'm sure they've given you plenty of legitimate material there, no?<br><br>See ya in Norrath.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
