<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100685923514477></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100685923514477><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100685923514477>RE: eq revisited</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100685923514477#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Sage>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>93 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Nov 27th 6:07 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.97]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><i>As for saying that eq is bussiness, DUHHHHHH. Of course it is, but the pursuit of money is bluring the goal of providing a service. <br></i>(sic)<br><br>You're <b>still</b> missing the point.  Providing a service is <b>not</b> the goal.  Making money is the goal.<br><br>Let me take you on a little detour.  We'll discuss a little classical psychology...<br>Freud suggested that the human psyche was composed of three components.  He called these the Id, the Ego and the SuperEgo.  These are successive stages of development.<br><LI>The Id is the initial childlike state.  <i>"I want it and I want it now!"</i>  It has no consideration.  It is purely desire.  (It's the nasty, grasping two-year-old, we each have inside us, clawing to get out.)<br><LI>The Ego is the devious state.  <i>"I can get that, if I do this, or if I wait, until it is unguarded!"</i>  It describes the level of development, where it is clear that grabbing a thing won't work.  So a plan is created.  (This is not to say it will necessarilly work.)  It is a level of subtlety and patience.<br><LI>The SuperEgo is a more esoteric thing.  It is the level of consciousness, where you feel good about doing good things and feel bad about doing bad things.  <i>(I'll not discuss this bit more, I only want the first two just now, really.)</i><br><b>An example...</b><br>I see a beautiful woman and I desire her...<br>The Id screams to take her now.  By whatever means necessary.  (Rapists live at the level of the Id!  (See, this stuff does have a practical use.))<br>The Ego is devious and cunning.  It recognises that what the Id wants cannot work.  But perhaps if you offer to buy the woman a drink and make amusing small-talk.  Then later you buy flowers.  And later still, you buy her a meal...<br>The SuperEgo is above all this, of course.  It rewards you, because when the woman dropped her shopping, you stopped to help.  (She walks away and you may never see her again, but you feel good, because you did something good.)  Or it punishes you, because you didn't help.  And you feel guilt.<br>End of detour...<br><br>Now, how does this psychological rambling fit in?  Businesses exist at the level of the Ego.  Sony/Verant are embodied by the Id.  They want money.  (Mine, your's, Pusbag's, everyone's.)  However, it is unlikely they will get it for nothing.  So they adopt the strategy of the Ego.  They do something, so people will give them money.  <i>(Don't be confused for an instant.  They do <b>not</b> do anything to provide a service.  Focus upon the goal!)</i>  <br>Now, do you remember when you were a kid and your mom told you you couldn't have a sweet, until you had done something?  (Tidy your room, the kitchen, take out bins, whatever...)  Do you remember how you would do the very minimum necessary to get the reward?  A business does the same.<br>There is no reason to fix PvP, because there isn't the need.  If and when the need develops, it will be fixed.  But, the need is defined by Cost Vs. Profits.  Not what you, I, or anyone else thinks.<br>The perfect example of this are the new SoL models.  People have been complaining that the new female models are unacceptable.  The thing to recognise here, is that Sony/Verant do not care if they offend anyone.  If a wood-elf model with big boobs and a kinky little leather harness creates more sales, that dropped customers, they will do it.  <i>(And it will!  Like it, or not, that is the truth.)</i><br><br>Anyhow, hopefully, that makes what I meant a <b>whole</b> lot clearer.<br><br>One last thing...<br><br><i>Contary to popular reader belief, most of my anti-eq reteric is NOT baseless.</i>(sic)<br><br>Now, I never said it was baseless.  To be honest, I think you've outgrown EQ, for whatever reason.  This being the case, you are no longer susceptable to it's positive aspects.<br><br>Anyhow, that's my bit for now.  *Grin*<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br><i>PS:  I thought you were going to start running your posts through a spell checker?  (Don't take this as a flame, but...)  There are a <b>lot</b> of spelling mistakes in your post.  It doesn't make it any less readable, but since you have taken the stance you have, you're putting yourself in line for a lot of grief.  Why add to it?  You and I both know that people will associate poor spelling with the idea that you're an eight-year-old moron, who has nothing better to do that troll.  (Don't even bother to answer that comment.  You'll just set yourself up!)  Write it in Word first and copy and paste.<br>PPS:  If anyone found the psychology even vaguely interesting, I strongly recommend you go have a wee read of some of Freud's stuff.  He's far more maligned than is justified.  Also he does have a lot of useful stuff to say that's quite entry level.  (Buy a primer of Freudian psychology.  It's worth it, believe me.)</i><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
