	   <tr><td colspan=2>(be sure to read part one before reading this)<br><br><br> Welcome to the giant rant part 2:<br><br>Well yesterday I discussed my eq history and my 3 biggest reasons for hating Verant Today, I am going to try answer some possible questions and criticisms you have brought up. Its shorter than part one, but that’s because I answered most of the issues last time.<br><br>“Eq is competing with Doac. Don’t you think that what they are doing is simple competition?”<br>Yes they are competing, but that does not mean that they should give up the vision in exchange for competing and resort to cheesy tactics . Dropping server counts to hide competition, “Project M”, the use of horses (I go into detail on this later) ect are all cheesy tactics, every one. Yes, Doac uses cheesy tactics but their a lot less blatant about doing it.  The key to competition in the Eq vs. Daoc debate is competing without looking like your throwing “bones” at players. EQ is blatantly throwing bones, Daoc is not; that’s the difference.<br><br>“Can’t you say that horses and capes should be a useful addition?<br>No and yes, Horses will be cool no doubt about it, but remember that horses are nothing but a 9 or 15k sow or selo’s. If I were still playing Lakanar, I would not touch one, because my sow is just as good.  If horses really did anything else maybe it would be worth it. Horses in Daoc are boats like in eq so until they put in player-controlled horses there is no comparison.<br><br>Capes just add to the character and help distinguish them from each other. I once met a shaman who looked almost exactly like me, except his spear was different, eriee looking to say that least. So capes and other distinguishing markers are good.<br> <br>“How do you feel about Daoc?”<br>I have a secret, I don’t play Doac that often!!!! Why? Because, I play other games and hangout with my friends (I would like to take this time to tell my girlfriend, that I love her J). The other reason is the main complaint about Doac, too much like eq. It’s just a superior eq. While eq was great, Doac improved on eq in several fronts: No more corpse runs, no more medding, better pvp.<br>	<br>Now people are bashing Daoc when it has been only one month. Sure Daoc shamans suck, sure Daoc Archers are over powered; but Mythic is trying as fast as they can. Verant took over two years to balance classes, and their still not done. They should save Luclin until classes are balanced; because with the addition of the beast lord, Verant’s balancing headaches are going to multiply.<br><br>Getting back to my original statement, I fee that Doac is just another eq and is not woth playing that much. Its good but it still has that boring monotonous gameplay feeling of Eq.  Which leads us into:<br>“What is the future of Roshi’s Rants?”<br>Well I will keep posting, but I am running out of ideas, once Luclin hits and I buy more games, I will have fresh ideas. So for now, Next week is the death of arcades and no update on the Friday after Thanksgiving.<br><br>“Any final thoughts on Verant and eq.” <br>Everquest was a good game that was marred when money got in the way of making a good game. If verant had not sat on their ass for some many years and only jumped up when REAL competition presented itself, I would not have been so mad. I do not regret playing eq. It gave me some fun experiences that I will not forget for a long time. Daoc is good, but its not really that incredibly good the really distinguish themselves from eq that well.<br>Thus ends the giant rant. Hope you have enjoyed reading it. <br>Roshi out.<br>P.S. let the slamming commence.<br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>current Doac Player;<br>Former eq player.</td></tr>
