<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100544197155461></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100544197155461><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100544197155461>Giant rant part one</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=91720&mid=100544197155461#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=91720><span id= >The One and Only roshi</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>86 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Nov 10th 8:26 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.25]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Because this rant is so big(just look at the size of part one) I am putting it up in two sections. First part today and second part in a few days.<br>Story part one: the happy years<br>   In July of 2000, I bought two games, the Sims and Everquest. Surprisingly enough Everquest was bought as an afterthought and I quickly abandoned the sims rather quickly. So I started playing Eq around mid-august. After fooling around with several characters(a wood-elf female ranger, an erudite wizard ect.) I settled on a human female warrior named…you guessed it ROSHI; now you know my namesake. While she was not powerful and did not have a piece of bronze on her by lvl 14 I enjoyed her greatly. She grew up around Freeport and went to crushbone too, I tried to run to Queynos forgot to bind in HH and was killed by Broon. Anyway I was so pissed I deleated her and started my shaman Lakanar. <br><br>    He grew up in Everfrost and Blackburrow and made his first trip to Freeport at lvl 9. About this time I joined a guild called the Prophets of Morrel-Thule, which would remain my guild for the next 21 levels until I got to 30(more on this later.) During my teen years I traveled allot, going from CB to Unrest to Oasis to Kurn’s tower(it was weird being the only barbarian in sight and having to use a slave to buy food.) to SK and back to Unrest where I gained twenty. After spending 20-23 in SK I moved, like most people to LOIO. Also about this time I re-started Roshi, except this time in Queynos instead of Freeport and she became my alt(and  my most well liked character by my guildmates, wonder why?). In Febuary when I gained 24(I was a slow leveler for several reason’s, a tough play rehearsal schedule my senior year is one of them.) I also became a guild officer and darkness began to show underneath the bright exterior to my eq playing experience.<br><br>Story part two: The end of morell-Thule.<br>     I spent 24-27 In LOIO(it took me two weeks Btw) and moved to Frontier mountain for 27-30. During this time in Frontier mountains Prophets of Morrel-Thule began to fall apart. Our leader Accursedsatyr, lost 15k worth of items that Verant would not reimburse. So he got mad at us for not helping him regain his items(I had 50pp to my name), so he left. I was also getting tired of people not listening to me, our raids, well, sucked. The two raids i had been on with them, always were plauged by low attendance and no-cohesion. At 30 I moved to ice-clad and was bugged-kicked from the guild. Well after I returned to it, people started in fighting and used me as a scape-goat. See while everyone else was living in glass houses I was willing to speak-out and that’s a no-no; so I left.<br>    <br>   After a short-stint in a guild I joined another guild called fortitude vindcit, which would be my guild from 32-38. I spent most of that time between EW and OT and a relatively decent time in my guild. Allot of my of old prophets members were in it and so it was good. Until I went on a Lguk raid in June where my guild(or a vengfull officer named Kakarato) executed one the worst backstabbing of my life. See we got in an arugment during the raid over an exe-hood. So I wanted it for roshi who, my guild helped me twink. While none else needed it Kakarato said no. I rolled along with a monk and a wizard named Maximus-floyd. Well after I won I dinged 38 left the raid and went to bed because it was 1 am.<br>    <br>   That morning I logged on twinked the hood to roshi and took her out on a croc spree in oasis and promptly was kicked out by kak. See this is where it gets good because I lost it. See Kak never said why he did just a vague “ we don’t like you now get lost and it am not alone”. Well it was sad because Kak helped me get totemic boots and was nice to me. When he would not say why i got mad. I promptly took lak out from the guild(he kicked Roshi out first ). Then I had some soul-searching to do. See most of FV had been my friend and now that I was gone there was no more incentive for me to play anymore. So I deleted them both, started a new account and moved to Terris-Thule where my dad and more 3 more months of fun await. Side note: I could have waited until Maximus-floyd or a girlfriend of an officer logged on and gotten promptly back in, but I wanted to play with my dad so I left.<br><br>Story part 3: Terris-thule and the end.<br>   <br>   It was sad being my enchanter on Terris-Thule, here I was yesterday I was a 38 shaman and now I had nothing except my dad to twink me. I lost so much I almost gave up, until Verant started a character transfer service(thanks Verant). So I reinstated my shaman and warrior and had them moved and on august 11 2001 Lakanar was re-Born (it would be a few more weeks until Roshi, now named roshix, would spawn again). My dad being the 40 druid that he was, twinked me with similar items, I got some other items on my own(nothing like a fresh blood-stained tunic) and started again. First I joined Warphoenix, while I was in Velious. WP was a good guild and I had fun with them the last 2 weeks of August.<br>    On August 29th 2001, I went to college. Because college is more time consuming (I don’t the hours and hours to play) I started to play less and less, though enough to gain 41(the last level gained in eq). While I was 40 I joined lllegendary Fate, because I befriended some of them but kept Roshix in Wp.  As the weeks  as a 41 stretched on, I became dissatisfied with Eq. Hunting wolf is GD was boring DL was to repetitive. I Tried SOLB, but nothing worked to help my dissatisfaction. I finally felt that I did not have the time to give and frankly I was bored with it and it was time to move on. So, on Oct. 10th 2001, I deleted my Eq account.  <br>    I wanted to believe there was some good in eq. I wanted to believe that I had not just thrown over a year worth of playing time down the drain. But everywhere I looked I just saw boring monotonous game play. Note I was not mad at <br>Verant at the time but I was what they did AFTER I left that made me angry. <br><br>Story part 4: why I am mad<br><br>I was not mad at Verant when I left, but I was getting there. Remember one of my first rants was on the deletions of the server numbers on September 23rdish; note this was not what made me mad.  What made me angry was three fold. First Melee and caster changes came out the day of DaoC release. I was mad at the fact that they waited years to fix stuff  they should have fixed from day one. The words ”the way we want them to be” was utter B.S to me. If Doac was never released they would have never done that and you know it.  <br><br>     Second, there was lessening of the night vision. This made me angry because they destroyed Brad’s “vision” in the name of competition. I bet Brad’s leaving had something to do with the destruction of his “vision”(pun not intended).  I had to put up with 41 levels of torches, serpents sights and ultravisions and now their gone; why, because it was an “inconvenience”. Night vision was more than just an inconvenience, it was a class balancing system and important part of how you play a Human Barbarian and Erudites.<br>    <br>     Finally and most recently there was project M. Forget about how great it is. Just look at it from a “vision” perspective. With the release of project M, it signaled the total disregard for the “vision”. It signaled that Verant no longer cared about creating a balanced game and fixing the problems within it, but throwing “bones” at players to get them to stay.<br>Thus ends part one. <br>Part 2: Where I stand on less important issues, Doac, MMORPGs in general and final sum up of my views on Verant and Eq.<br>Please save all question and "eq is competing with doac" comments until after part 2 where all your question will hopefully be answered.<br>Roshi out.<br>&nbsp;<br>current Doac Player;<br>Former eq player.</td></tr>
