	   <tr><td colspan=2>I somewhat frequently read your journal.  Most times I feel it is a waste of my time, not flaming you or your intentions, it is just that I only play EQ and I do like most parts of it.  Since I never before had much opportunity to play many games (49 year old father) I have put far too much time into Eq (ask the Mrs.!).  There are aspects Verant has that I feel are cheats on their part, solely used because they do not desire to clean up their game.  Such as a cat attacking you through the walls?  You standing on a building and able to attack without fear a punishable exploit?  Silly!  If I can't attack through a wall then they can't either.  The same functions that keep me from attacking or passing should be used by all.  If you don't want me to use the resources available, correct it, don't penalize someone that has worked to find the most efficient method of assault.<br><br>Rant off<br><br>Perhaps some day I will play some of the other games.  Will I let your opinions influence my enjoyment?  That would be stupid on my part.  That would be the equivalent of agreeing that an ugly woman is less a woman than a pretty one.  Play the games, accept the 'faults' and enjoy or leave the games.<br><br>Concering Star Wars.  Excellent film.  Can it be devalued by marketing toys and games, only for those that will not seperate the movie from the marketing.  I don't care how many dolls or games they make.  If the movie, which this is, is of calibre to be great, it will remain great only because the viewer enjoys it.  If the movie falters after a game's release it is because you, unlike before, was not able to place yourself witin the framework of the movie.  The movie did not change, you did.  So clear your ming, relax, and be just as awed of the introduction and the great ship flying onto the screen as you did before.<br><br>Well perhaps I have spoken too much.  I do like your journal, though perhaps not so much your boasting about threads.  Please keep it up.<br><br>Laleldil Tremulous 49cleric<br>Lenelor 11 shaman<br>Boulderdash 13 enchanter<br>Lalscourier 8 warrior<br>Bobbert 1 Wizard<br>&nbsp;<br>A simple cleric of Rodcet Nif on Tholuxe Paells</td></tr>
